-- Man City Plans $59 Million Bid for Hazard, Digne, Sun Reports
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-04-08T11:49:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-08/man-city-plans-59-million-bid-for-hazard-digne-sun-reports.html
Manchester City  plans to make a 37
million-pound ($59 million) double bid for Lille’s Eden Hazard
and Lucas Digne, the Sun  reported , without saying where it got
the information.  City manager Roberto Mancini wants to bolster his squad
after losing key players to international duty and injuries this
season, the newspaper said.  Mancini has already spent 210 million pounds on players in
two years since joining the Premier League soccer club, the Sun
reported.   He has watched Belgian winger Hazard and also wants 18-
year-old fullback Digne who has recently broken into Lille’s
first team, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 James Cone  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  